{"kind":"symbol","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/AstronomyKit\/documentation\/AstronomyKit"]]},"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Enumeration","title":"Chiron","symbolKind":"enum","role":"symbol","externalID":"s:12AstronomyKit6ChironO","fragments":[{"text":"enum","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Chiron","kind":"identifier"}],"modules":[{"name":"AstronomyKit"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Chiron","kind":"identifier"}]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Provides position calculations for 2060 Chiron."}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/astronomykit\/chiron"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Chiron"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"text":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Chiron is a minor planet (centaur) orbiting between Saturn and Uranus.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Since Astronomy Engine doesn’t include Chiron as a built-in body,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"positions are calculated using gravity simulation with pre-computed","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"state vectors from JPL Horizons.","type":"text"}]},{"text":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Chiron’s position is computed by:"}]},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Selecting the nearest reference epoch to the requested time"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Initializing a gravity simulation at that epoch"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Propagating to the requested time"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Converting to the desired coordinate system","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"text":"Accuracy","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Accuracy"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Accuracy is highest near the reference epochs (2000, 2010, 2020, 2030, 2040)"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and degrades slightly as distance from these epochs increases due to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"numerical integration error. For typical usage within ±5 years of an epoch,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"error is expected to be less than 1 arcminute."}]},{"text":"Example","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Example"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ Get Chiron's ecliptic longitude","let longitude = try Chiron.eclipticLongitude(at: .now)","print(\"Chiron is at \\(longitude)°\")","","\/\/ Get Chiron's geocentric position","let position = try Chiron.geoPosition(at: .now)","print(\"Chiron position: \\(position)\")"]}],"kind":"content"}],"topicSections":[{"anchor":"Type-Methods","title":"Type Methods","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/AstronomyKit\/documentation\/AstronomyKit\/Chiron\/ecliptic(at:)","doc:\/\/AstronomyKit\/documentation\/AstronomyKit\/Chiron\/eclipticLatitude(at:)","doc:\/\/AstronomyKit\/documentation\/AstronomyKit\/Chiron\/eclipticLongitude(at:)","doc:\/\/AstronomyKit\/documentation\/AstronomyKit\/Chiron\/equatorial(at:)","doc:\/\/AstronomyKit\/documentation\/AstronomyKit\/Chiron\/geoPosition(at:)","doc:\/\/AstronomyKit\/documentation\/AstronomyKit\/Chiron\/geoState(at:)","doc:\/\/AstronomyKit\/documentation\/AstronomyKit\/Chiron\/helioPosition(at:)","doc:\/\/AstronomyKit\/documentation\/AstronomyKit\/Chiron\/horizon(at:from:refraction:)"]}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"sections":[],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/AstronomyKit\/documentation\/AstronomyKit\/Chiron","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"references":{"doc://AstronomyKit/documenta